# UPI Transaction Analytics Project

This project contains a modular database schema design and analytical SQL suite for auditing UPI transaction data, identifying seasonal patterns, auditing fraud rates, profiling merchant performance, and preparing data dashboards.

## 📂 Project Structure

The project is divided into logical, easy-to-understand files:

```
c:\Users\HP\Desktop\New folder (2)\
├── schema\
│   ├── 01_create_database.sql       - Database creation & raw staging table schema.
│   ├── 02_import_instructions.sql    - Guides & SQL command for importing the CSV file.
│   ├── 03_create_transactions.sql   - Final structured transactions table & casting.
│   ├── 04_data_quality_checks.sql   - Duplicate checks, null assessments, & delete cleaning.
│   └── 05_create_lookup_table.sql   - Storing regional lookup references.
├── analysis\
│   ├── 01_monthly_growth.sql        - MoM performance using CTEs & window functions.
│   ├── 02_state_region_volume.sql   - Volume & regional rollup spend aggregations.
│   ├── 03_peak_hours.sql            - Traffic density comparison (weekday vs weekend).
│   ├── 04_merchant_category.sql     - Category spending rank & revenue percentage.
│   ├── 05_fraud_patterns.sql        - Fraud flags by state, hardware, and outliers.
│   ├── 06_ops_metrics.sql           - Failure vs success rate operational KPIs.
│   └── 07_power_bi_export.sql       - consolidated database view for exporting data.
├── run_all.sql                      - Sequential copy-paste script for quick execution.
└── README.md                        - This document.
```

