## 📈 Running the Analyses

Each analytics topic resides in its own script under the `/analysis` folder:

1. **MoM Volume Growth:** [01_monthly_growth.sql](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/New%20folder%20(2)/analysis/01_monthly_growth.sql)  
   Uses standard CTEs and the window function `LAG()` to calculate the month-over-month growth of transaction spends.
2. **State & Region Performance:** [02_state_region_volume.sql](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/New%20folder%20(2)/analysis/02_state_region_volume.sql)  
   Joins geographical dimension keys to show aggregate spend count, sum, and average spend sizes.
3. **Hourly Peaks:** [03_peak_hours.sql](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/New%20folder%20(2)/analysis/03_peak_hours.sql)  
   Aggregates transaction volumes across 24-hour periods and splits them into weekday vs weekend groups.
4. **Merchant Spend Dominance:** [04_merchant_category.sql](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/New%20folder%20(2)/analysis/04_merchant_category.sql)  
   Ranks merchants via windowed SUM totals to demonstrate which product categories capture the largest market share.
5. **Fraud and Outlier Audits:** [05_fraud_patterns.sql](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/New%20folder%20(2)/analysis/05_fraud_patterns.sql)  
   Calculates fraud percentages by geography or device-network pairs. The statistical outlier check filters transactions exceeding:
   $$\mu + 3\sigma$$
   (Mean + 3 Standard Deviations)
6. **Platform Performance KPIs:** [06_ops_metrics.sql](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/New%20folder%20(2)/analysis/06_ops_metrics.sql)  
   Calculates system-wide success and failure rates.

